---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="Shelly privacy summary for terminal content, pairing, push notifications, telemetry, and encrypted local persistence."
>
  <section class="page">
    <div class="page-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Terminal content stays out of push and relay control planes.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Shelly is designed around a narrow data path: terminal bytes move only between
        the host daemon and paired clients over encrypted transport. Push providers receive
        fixed generic copy and opaque hashes.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-list">
      <article class="tile">
        <h3>Terminal data</h3>
        <p>PTY input and output stay on the host unless a paired iroh client attaches to the session.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="tile">
        <h3>Pairing</h3>
        <p>The QR carries a compact `sh1` pairing ticket with reachability plus a 5-character Crockford code. The code expires after 5 minutes, wrong attempts are capped, and long-lived access uses the paired iroh node identity that can be revoked from the desktop CLI.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="tile">
        <h3>Push</h3>
        <p>Push payloads contain only event type, fixed alert text, and opaque hashes. They never include terminal content, commands, paths, session names, or `last_line`.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="tile">
        <h3>Telemetry</h3>
        <p>Daemon and mobile crash reporting are not bundled in v1. Relay telemetry is aggregate-only.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="tile">
        <h3>Local storage</h3>
        <p>Scrollback and paired-device records are encrypted locally by default. Keychain prompts are only for local key material; terminal output, keystrokes, commands, paths, session names, and push tokens are not stored there. The daemon keeps persistence directories and database files private and rejects symlinked stores.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
